<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WORLD; 
</P>
<P>
'GREENHOUSE' PERIL STRESSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A U.N. report said that it is too late to halt all the effects from global 
warming and that nations should begin to prepare for rising sea levels and crop 
damage expected from the "greenhouse effect." Experts who submitted the report 
to a meeting in Kenya of the U.N. Environment Program's governing council 
reiterated the need to slow down the rate of climatic warming by such measures 
as encouraging a switch away from fossil fuels. They also said that rising 
oceans could inundate lands now settled by 1 billion people in the next 60 
years and urged governments to discourage large-scale coastal developments and 
get ready to help existing seaside enterprises that eventually have to be 
abandoned. 
</P>
</TEXT>
