<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE STATE; 
</P>
<P>
AETNA ENDS ITS MORATORIUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Aetna Life &amp; Casualty, the ninth-largest seller of property and casualty 
insurance in California, said that it is resuming sales to new customers of 
auto, homeowner and commercial liability policies. The announcement ended a 
two-week moratorium on such sales while the company evaluated how the state 
Supreme Court decision upholding most of Proposition 103 would be enforced. A 
company spokesman said Aetna had concluded from statements made May 11 by state 
Insurance Commissioner Roxani Gillespie that the state intends to allow the 
insurance industry a fair rate of return in California for each line of 
insurance. Numerous insurers have expressed satisfaction at Gillespie's 
decision to allow a profit for each line of insurance, while a number of 
consumer groups have criticized the decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
