<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: ESPOSITO IS FIRED BY NEW YORK RANGERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phil Esposito was fired Wednesday as coach, general manager and vice president 
of the New York Rangers after a tenure marked by his many trades. 
</P>
<P>
Esposito was fired less than two months after receiving a vote of confidence 
from Madison Square Garden Sports Group, which owns the hockey team. 
</P>
<P>
Esposito, who never led the team past the first round of the Stanley Cup 
playoffs, said the firing left him "in some ways relieved, in other ways 
frustrated." 
</P>
<P>
Esposito, 47, had one year remaining on his contract. 
</P>
</TEXT>
