<HEADLINE>
<P>
CHARITY SCORECARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Bea Maxwell 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Bruin classic held at MGM Filmland on May 13 netted $163,000 for the UCLA 
Intervention Program for Handicapped Children. Kathy Hampar was chairwoman. 
Auction chairs were Geraldine Gross and Ruth Lebowitz. 
</P>
<P>
The Second City benefit performance held at Mayfair Music Hall on May 16 netted 
$33,000 for Westside Children's Center, an organization that recruits parents 
to care for abused children. Martin and Nancy Short hosted the event. 
</P>
<P>
The benefit gala held on May 17 at the Japanese American Cultural &amp; 
Community Center in Little Tokyo netted between $80,000 and $90,000 for the 
center. Mistress of Ceremonies was Kathryn Doi Todd. 
</P>
<P>
The benefit dinner for the Churchill Foundation at the Beverly Hilton on May 17 
netted more than $850,000 for scholarships and fellowships for American 
graduate students to study at Cambridge University. 
</P>
<P>
The "Phantom of the Opera" benefit at The Music Center on May 20 netted an 
estimated $750,000 for the Center Theatre Group. Nancy Vreeland and Terri 
Childs were co-chairwomen. 
</P>
<P>
The benefit ball for ARCS (Achievement Rewards for College Scientists) held on 
May 20 at the Regent Beverly Wilshire netted $475,000. Nadine Acker was 
chairwoman. 
</P>
<P>
The 36th annual SHARE Boomtown Party held on May 20 at Santa Monica Civic 
Auditorium netted an estimated $1.2 million for programs for the retarded and 
other charities SHARE supports. Pam Korman and Roni Sue Malin were co-chairs. 
</P>
<P>
Concern Foundation's 15th Annual Rodeo Block Party on May 21 raised almost 
$750,000 for cancer research. Rebecca Golden, Anne Barnett and Mathew Schryro 
co-chaired. 
</P>
<P>
The 10th Annual Venice Art Walk held on May 21 netted an estimated $600,000 for 
the Venice Family Clinic. Sheila Goldberg was chairwoman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
