<HEADLINE>
<P>
CONTEST; 
</P>
<P>
GARLIC FEST DEADLINE IS JUNE 25 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Entries for the Great Garlic Recipe Contest and Cook-Off, part of the Gilroy 
Garlic Festival, are being accepted through June 25. 
</P>
<P>
The festival runs from July 28 to 30, with the cook-off held on July 29. 
</P>
<P>
First prize winner will receive $1,000, second prize, $500 and third prize 
$300. An additional $100 prize will be awarded for the best recipe using the 
most garlic. Finalists will be reimbursed for cost of ingredients and one 
night's lodging in Gilroy, where the cook-off will take place. 
</P>
<P>
Each recipe must contain at least three cloves of fresh garlic or its 
equivalent in processed garlic. Original recipes or original variations of 
classic recipes may be submitted. 
</P>
<P>
Send typed or printed recipes on 8 1/2x11-inch paper to: Recipe Contest 1989, 
Gilroy Garlic Festival, P.O. Box 2311, Gilroy, Calif. 95020. 
</P>
<P>
Entrants unable to come to Gilroy to compete are eligible to win one of four 
$75 prizes. These entries should be marked "Regional Competition Only." 
</P>
</TEXT>
