<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRITAIN, IRELAND PLEDGE TO STEP UP FIGHT ON IRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
BELFAST, Northern Ireland 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Britain and the Irish Republic pledged Wednesday to tighten cross-border 
cooperation in a determined bid to combat the outlawed Irish Republican Army. 
</P>
<P>
In a joint statement issued after a meeting at Belfast's Stormont Castle to 
review the 1985 Anglo-Irish accord, the two governments condemned "in the 
strongest terms" the use of violence for political ends. 
</P>
</TEXT>
