<TEXT>
<P>
Malibu business leaders who elected Martin Sheen honorary mayor last month, 
looking forward to a little high-profile promotion, are now talking about 
"impeaching" him and replacing him with Johnny Carson. The Malibu Chamber of 
Commerce picked Sheen last month to promote its "Shop Malibu" campaign and to 
make appearances at civic affairs. Instead, the actor, known for his liberal 
activism, declared Malibu a nuclear-free zone. The recall drive gained momentum 
when Sheen called for the beachside haven of the stars to become a "sanctuary 
for aliens and the homeless." Meanwhile, the roadside marquee for the Malibu 
Inn and Restaurant, which last week urged "Dump Martin Sheen," read earlier 
this week: "Johnny for Mayor." Carson says he's not interested in any 
mayorship, honorary or otherwise. Claudia Puig 
