<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: TV &amp; VIDEO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Claudia Puig, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chicago Sun-Times has dropped a gossip columnist who reported a rumor 
involving television talk-show host Oprah Winfrey. Columnist Ann Gerber's 
column was discontinued over "basic differences" with Kenneth Towers, vice 
president and executive editor, "involving the journalistic standards used in 
producing her column," the newspaper said Tuesday night. Gerber's "On the Town" 
column was run on a free-lance basis. This month she reported a rumor that 
Winfrey had returned home unexpectedly and caught her boyfriend in a tryst with 
her hairdresser. Winfrey issued a strongly worded denial on her nationally 
syndicated show. Gerber reportedly said in a subsequent television interview 
that she had no confirmation for the rumor but ran the item because it was 
being talked about. Claudia Puig 
</P>
