<HEADLINE>
<P>
DIGEST: LONG BEACH; 
</P>
<P>
COUNTY ALLOCATES GRANTS FOR HOMELESS PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The County Board of Supervisors on Tuesday approved $45,000 in grants for 
homeless programs in Long Beach and Venice. Another $5,000 will go to a food 
bank at a community and senior citizens center in east Compton. 
</P>
<P>
The allocations come from $50,000 set aside annually for homeless agencies in 
each of the five supervisorial districts. 
</P>
<P>
On Supervisor Deane Dana's recommendation, the Low Income and Elderly Community 
Assistance Center on Westminster Avenue in Venice was awarded $23,000, while 
the downtown Long Beach Homeless Shelter on Chestnut Avenue will get $22,000 
this year. 
</P>
<P>
The board also awarded $8,330 to the Long Beach Council PTA drug education 
program and $10,000 for the city of Lakewood to develop an anti-gang and drug 
video to be shown to community groups. 
</P>
</TEXT>
