<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: CULVER CITY; 
</P>
<P>
CONSTRUCTION BAN UPHELD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
After going into executive session to review a recently imposed 90-day ban on 
the construction of apartments with four or more units, the City Council voted 
to uphold the ordinance and deny an appeal from three developers seeking 
exemptions from the moratorium. 
</P>
<P>
In addition to the ban on apartments with four or more units, the interim 
ordinance also imposes size limits and open-space requirements for buildings 
with two or three units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
