<P>
DIGEST: CERRITOS; 
</P>
<P>
MEHTA WINS APPOINTMENT TO STATE SCHOOL BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Gov. George Deukmejian has appointed Paras Mehta of Cerritos as the student 
representative on the state Board of Education. 
</P>
<P>
Mehta, 15, will serve as a voting member of the board for one year until his 
term expires in August, 1990. The appointment will require state Senate 
confirmation. He replaces student representative Maryela Martinez of Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
Mehta, a junior at Cerritos High School in the ABC Unified School District, was 
most recently announced as the winner in a United Nations essay contest. 
</P>
<P>
He is a member of the Model United Nations Club, the California Scholastic 
Federation and Mu Alpha Theta, an international math society. 
</P>
</TEXT>
