<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: SANTA MONICA; 
</P>
<P>
AUDITORIUM CROWD CONTROL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Armed with a "Dear Abby" column, City Councilwoman Christine Reed is demanding 
that the city do something about crowd control at the Santa Monica Civic 
Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
A Sherman Oaks resident wrote to the advice columnist in early May, citing the 
dangers of a "churning riptide of humanity" at a concert in the auditorium less 
than a month after unruly crowds at a soccer match in Sheffield, England, left 
93 people dead. 
</P>
<P>
The reader said a similar tragedy could occur at concerts at the Santa Monica 
Civic Auditorium. 
</P>
