<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: DUARTE; 
</P>
<P>
SKATEBOARD BAN AT CITY HALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Skateboarders will be banned from the City Hall complex, under an ordinance 
adopted by the City Council on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
The ban is intended to save curbs, steps and handrails from abuse by youths who 
turn the complex into a skateboard park on weekends, said Assistant City 
Manager Manuel Ontal. Steps have been chipped, and wide handrails have been 
damaged by skateboarders who use them as ramps, he said. 
</P>
<P>
The ordinance, which takes effect in 30 days, imposes a $100-fine for a 
first-time offense and a $200-fine if it is repeated within a year. The 
skateboard would also be confiscated until it is no longer needed as evidence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
