<P>
NBC WINS MAY NETWORK SWEEPS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NBC won the May television sweeps, matching its own record for the widest 
margin of victory ever, it was announced today. CBS came in second and ABC was 
third. 
</P>
<P>
The TV sweeps, during which the ratings companies measure viewing in about 200 
local markets, form the basis for local advertising rates and to a lesser 
degree influence network prices. NBC had a 24% margin of victory over CBS and 
28% over ABC, matching its own record margin over the second-place contender a 
year ago, said Gerry Jaffe, NBC vice president for research. 
</P>
